>3 sec\/speed 7<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula."},{"content":"Add shrimp paste, peanut butter, coconut milk, soy sauce, ketchup and sesame oil and cook <b>10 min\/212°F\/speed 3<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Clean mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"For Pizza"},{"content":"Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in chicken and 2 tbsp. reserved satay sauce and mix together coating chicken. Set aside."},{"content":"Preheat oven to 500°F. Grease two pizza pans with oil (see Tip)."},{"content":"Divide dough in half and place onto prepared pans. Stretch dough out to pan edges, with lightly floured fingers. Cover with clean kitchen towels and let rise 5 minutes."},{"content":"Place 6 oz provolone into mixing bowl and grate <b>5 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Again, place 6 oz provolone into mixing bowl and grate <b>5 sec\/speed 8<b>. Transfer to bowl with previously grated cheese and set aside."},{"content":"Spread 6 tbsp reserved satay sauce evenly over one pizza base and leave other covered. Arrange half the red and green peppers evenly over pizza and top with half the marinated chicken pieces. Sprinkle with half the grated cheese. Bake for 8-10 minutes (500°F). Repeat with remaining dough. Serve warm."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Satay sauce can be stored in an airtight container for up to one week in the refrigerator.","Freeze baked pizza and reheat for 7-9 minutes (500°F).","If using a sheet pan divide dough into thirds and make three (12 in.) pizzas. To make four individual (9 in.) pizzas, divide dough into quarters and shape onto a sheet pan with parchment sprinkled with semolina.","If using a pizza stone, follow manufacturer's instructions.","Replace yellow onion with red onion.","Garnish with chopped cilantro."],"basicInfo":["medium","20m","55m","2 pieces"]}